The party rushed the doors. The Deathlords moved to interceptΓÇöancient warriors wielding weapons that predated kingdoms. But they were outnumbered. Galmar engaged one directly while Kyboah, Ylva, and the others swarmed the second.
The Deathlords were formidable. They moved with the skill of warriors who'd trained for centuries, their ancient blades finding gaps in armor with precision. But against the combined might of the Wardens and Galmar Stone-Fist, even legendary guardians couldn't hold.
When both Deathlords finally fell, Galmar kicked the massive iron doors open.
Behind them, the crypt still echoed with fighting. The archers on the catwalks. The spawners they hadn't destroyed. The ongoing chaos.
But ahead was the throne room. And the Crown.
They stepped through, Alfonso's sixteen plague ghouls shambling after them, and the doors slammed shut.

PART VI: THE BREAKER
The Inner Sanctum
The throne room vibrated with a deafening, rhythmic scream of metal tearing into stone. GRIND. THUD. GRIND. THUD. The sound rattled teeth and made the very air taste of copper and ozone.
In the center of the chamber, clamped directly onto the sacred vault door, a massive boring machine churned. Brass gears spun and pistons fired, driving iron teeth into ancient rock, powered by soul gems that pulsed with sick, radioactive green light.
Beside the machine stood a titan.
Seven feet of grey-green Orcish muscle loomed over the controls, encased in a suit of Ancient Dragonplate armor. The massive bone plates were bolted directly into his skeletal system, the skin around the connection points scarred and weeping translucent amber fluid. He smelled of pine resin and burning oil.
He continued his work as the doors crashed open, his massive armored hands adjusting a delicate pressure valve with watchmaker precision, ignoring the violent vibrations and the arrival of an army at his back.
Galmar stepped forward, leveling his warhammer. "FACE YOUR DEATH, ABOMINATION!"
The figure froze. His hand locked on the valve.
SlowlyΓÇöwith the heavy, hydraulic whine of a siege engine rotatingΓÇöhe turned.
